  "2026-07-12T23:37:43.406Z",codex-pm-audit-extraction,"E2E evidence: isolated temp project bare core rejected dedupe-audit and exposed no audit flags; pm install audit activated cleanly; package doctor OK; dedupe-audit, comments-audit, normalize, update help, and files help restored expected package surface."
  "2026-07-13T00:37:01.319Z",codex-pm-audit-extraction,"Verification evidence: pnpm release:gates reached 278 test files / 5592 tests with literal 100% statement, branch, function, and line coverage; typecheck, docs/skills, static quality, token budget, and isolated package installation all pass. Existing scripts/reviews/pr-review-loop.mjs and docs/PR_REVIEW_LOOP.md are linked for the hosted bot acknowledgement loop."
  "2026-07-13T01:21:50.923Z",codex-pm-audit-extraction,"Final local verification evidence: node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 278 test files and 5,593 tests with literal 100% statements (35,360/35,360), branches (25,334/25,334), functions (7,141/7,141), and lines (34,585/34,585). The package-owned linked_artifact_audit service now contains files/docs aggregation; bare core only dispatches the optional service."
  "2026-07-13T02:02:01.842Z",codex-pm-audit-extraction,"Hosted review loop 1: Greptile found a valid P1 normalize ownership-bypass mapping regression and stale completion/guidance artifacts; CodeRabbit supplied 14 inline findings plus outside-diff suggestions. Valid findings were implemented, including append-only bypass enforcement, generic release result naming, package service types, completion repair, parity assertions, and package docs. The package-only MCP-field suggestion was refused because adding those keys to the default schema would violate pm-vjk3's bare-core boundary. Gemini and CodeRabbit quota notices will be acknowledged individually. Local feedback verification: focused 159 tests passed, contracts snapshot current, lint/static/token gates passed; full release:gates reached 5,593 tests and 100% coverage, then correctly stopped only because its Greptile gate reviewed the still-uncommitted previous head."
  "2026-07-13T02:09:11.325Z",codex-pm-audit-extraction,"Continuation started: preserving inherited review fixes, reopening the boundary inventory despite earlier green evidence, and treating PR #536 current-head bot/CI convergence plus merge as unfinished acceptance work."
  "2026-07-13T03:15:20.726Z",codex-pm-audit-extraction,"Fresh local evidence on the expanded boundary pass: pnpm lint passed; audit package boundary and token/static gates passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 279 files and 5,602 tests at exactly 100% statements (35,417/35,417), branches (25,409/25,409), functions (7,152/7,152), and lines (34,638/34,638); pnpm release:gates passed completely, including type/package/example checks, docs/skills, secrets, packed npx smoke, and the 88-command package-first dogfood run. A separate temp workspace proved bare core rejects dedupe-audit and exposes no --audit/--allow-audit flags, while installing packages/pm-governance-audit restores command/flag help and returns linked_by_count=2 for a shared file. The new scripts/release/audit-package-boundary.mjs ratchets exact audit execution/API tokens out of src and PRD."
  "2026-07-13T03:50:29.758Z",codex-pm-audit-extraction,"Hosted review loop 2 dispositions: all inventoried bot comments, reviews, and 18 inline findings were individually up/down-voted and replied to; all threads are resolved. Greptile current-head check passed with no actionable findings. CodeRabbit valid follow-ups implemented: actionable package SDK load error, escaped PRD table separator, ownershipDependencyBypass normalization, finally-safe extension registry cleanup, and typed normalize adapter. Its stale shared-mode observation revealed title_exact/title_fuzzy/parent_scope still in the bare MCP mode enum; those audit-only values were removed from core and added to the boundary ratchet. The proposal to expose package bypass fields in default MCP/SDK contracts was refused because it violates pm-vjk3; the redundant decorator catch was refused because runActiveServiceOverride already preserves the completed result and centralizes warnings. Verification: focused 192 tests and lint pass; regenerated contract is audit-mode clean; the full release gate again passed 279 files / 5,602 tests at exact 100% coverage plus all packed/dogfood gates. Only the final optional Greptile CLI subprocess returned nonzero because it excluded the 8 uncommitted fixes and then its external review service failed unexpectedly; hosted Greptile on the pushed head remained green. Next: commit/push these fixes, retrigger all hosted bots, and wait for the complete new-head window."
  "2026-07-13T04:19:17.205Z",codex-pm-audit-extraction,"Hosted review loop 3: Greptile edited its summary with a valid P1 proving parser-derived package bypass options were dropped before core action execution. Fixed by syncing parser and preflight options back into Commander before action arguments are consumed; added a focused wrapped-action regression and strengthened the installed audit package integration so a foreign-owner update fails normally, then succeeds with --allow-audit-update and returns audit_update=true. New Gemini quota and CodeRabbit completion comments were up-voted and acknowledged; the edited Greptile comment retained its up-vote and received a fresh detailed disposition. Verification: focused 199 tests pass, static quality/boundary/token gates pass, and full coverage passes 279 files / 5,603 tests at exact 100% across statements, branches, functions, and lines."
  "2026-07-13T04:48:51.858Z",codex-pm-audit-extraction,"Final hosted evidence on be232cb0: every required GitHub Actions/security/docs/CodeQL/Semgrep/CodeFactor/Codecov check is green, including Ubuntu Node 22/24, macOS Node 24, Windows Node 24, all four coverage shards, static/type/compat/smoke gates, Trivy, actionlint, ShellCheck, and PSScriptAnalyzer. Greptile re-reviewed the parser fix at 5/5 with no findings and explicitly safe to merge; CodeRabbit completed green after its final typed-normalizer suggestion was implemented; Gemini responded with its free-tier quota notice and no finding; Sourcery/Cubic explicitly skipped by service limits. Every bot comment/review/inline finding was voted and replied to, edited summaries were rechecked, and zero review threads remain unresolved. Local final proof remains 279 files / 5,603 tests at exact 100% coverage plus installed-package cross-owner update, release, and linked-artifact audit behavior."
